    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My main use case is to edit magic cells in terminal ipython.\n\nSome alternatives are:\n1. Special parameter to `%edit` cells. Say `%edit -c sh`.\n2. Some hot key to open an external editor (say vim) while editing, with the current ongoing edition (that would be very useful in a lot of cases! As in bash `fc` which can be bound to some key). \n"
  },
