    "body": "%edit doesn't recognize the .ipy extension, just .py which makes sense considering it will exec the contents. For the -r case I think it's sensible to recognize .ipy as a file extension.\n\nJust out of curiosity, there is ptipython, which is the advantage of using pt internally? Will it work in all jupyter clients? And will you still support readline?\n"
