    "created_at": "2015-12-28T11:03:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-28T11:03:17Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, it probably makes sense to be able to do `%edit foo.ipy`. There's no need for the `-r` flag, that's just to get the raw format when you're editing from history (e.g. `%edit -r 2-7`).\n\nI know of ptipython, and we're basically going to fold the technology into ipython itself and make ptipython obsolete. prompt_toolkit is for terminal interaction, so it's not relevant to jupyter clients like the notebook or the Qt console. I plan to work it into terminal IPython first, and later jupyter_console. I expect that we will eventually drop support for readline, because it's an awkward dependency (we have [a docs section](http://ipython.readthedocs.org/en/stable/install/install.html#dependencies) specific to installing it) and prompt_toolkit is more capable.\n"
  },
