    "updated_at": "2016-01-01T20:37:00Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A mapping from file extensions to cell magics could be kept and those file types could be evaluated using their magics. This would provide with powerfull cell editing in the console. The raw editing solution I proposed above is somewhat lacking because it implies to type the cell heading and to lose editor features contextual to the file type, because of the ipy extension. What do you think? I could code this and make a pr if you agree.\n\nI'm glad you're adding prompt_toolkit support and that eventually it will make its way into the jupyter console, but please never drop good old readline support as the julia guys did.\n"
